cog-description: Words that rhyme with, mean, or sound like something (and more!)
words-description: Words that rhyme with, mean, or sound like something (and more!). Run `{0}help words`
words-help:
Usage: `{0}words <command>: <string>` (or `{0}words <command> <string>` where `<string>` has no spaces)
`<command>` can be one of:`

**`that rhyme with`**
**`rhyme`**
**`rhy`**
**`nry`**
Words that rhyme with a word.

**`that mean`**
**`means`**
**`ml`**
Words that mean something.

**`that sound like`**
**`sounds`**
**`sl`**
Words that sound like something.

**`spelled like`**
**`spelled`**
**`sp`**
Words that are spelled like something.

**`modified by`**
**`jja`**
Popular nouns modified by the given adjective, per Google Books Ngrams.

**`that modify`**
**`modifying`**
**`jjb`**
Popular adjectives used to modify the given noun, per Google Books Ngrams.

**`associated with`**
**`triggered by`**
**`trg`**
Words that are statistically associated with the query word in the same piece of text.

**`that follow`**
**`following`**
**`after`**
**`bga`**
Words that frequently follow the given word (per Google Books Ngrams).

**`that precede`**
**`preceding`**
**`before`**
**`bgb`**
Frequent predecessors of the given word (per Google Books Ngrams).
hypernyms-description: Hypernyms (words that are more general than the word, per WordNet)
hyponyms-description: Hyponyms (words that are more specific than the word, per WordNet)
holonyms-description: Holonyms (words that are a part of the word, per WordNet)
meronyms-description: Meronyms (words that the word is part of, per WordNet)
